  "id": "guide/router-store/install",
  "title": "Installation",
  "contents": "\n\n\n  <div class=\"github-links\">\n    <a href=\"https://github.com/ngrx/platform/edit/master/projects/ngrx.io/content/guide/router-store/install.md?message=docs%3A%20describe%20your%20change...\" aria-label=\"Suggest Edits\" title=\"Suggest Edits\"><i class=\"material-icons\" aria-hidden=\"true\" role=\"img\">mode_edit</i></a>\n  </div>\n\n\n<div class=\"content\">\n<h1 id=\"installation\">Installation<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/router-store/install#installation\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h1>\n<h2 id=\"installing-with-ng-add\">Installing with <code>ng add</code><a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/router-store/install#installing-with-ng-add\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<p>You can install the Router Store to your project with the following <code>ng add</code> command <a href=\"https://angular.io/cli/add\" target=\"_blank\">(details here)</a>:</p>\n<code-example language=\"sh\">\nng add @ngrx/router-store@latest\n</code-example>\n<h3 id=\"optional-ng-add-flags\">Optional <code>ng add</code> flags<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/router-store/install#optional-ng-add-flags\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h3>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>flag</th>\n<th>description</th>\n<th>value type</th>\n<th>default value</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><code>--path</code></td>\n<td>Path to the module that you wish to add the import for the <code><a href=\"api/router-store/StoreRouterConnectingModule\" class=\"code-anchor\">StoreRouterConnectingModule</a></code> to.</td>\n<td><code>string</code></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code>--project</code></td>\n<td>Name of the project defined in your <code>angular.json</code> to help locating the module to add the <code><a href=\"api/router-store/StoreRouterConnectingModule\" class=\"code-anchor\">StoreRouterConnectingModule</a></code> to.</td>\n<td><code>string</code></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code>--module</code></td>\n<td>Name of file containing the module that you wish to add the import for the <code><a href=\"api/router-store/StoreRouterConnectingModule\" class=\"code-anchor\">StoreRouterConnectingModule</a></code> to. Can also include the relative path to the file. For example, <code>src/app/app.module.ts</code>.</td>\n<td><code>string</code></td>\n<td><code>app</code></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><code>--standalone</code></td>\n<td>Flag to configure <code>@ngrx/router-store</code> in the standalone application config.</td>\n<td><code>boolean</code></td>\n<td><code>false</code></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>This command will automate the following steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Update <code>package.json</code> > <code>dependencies</code> with <code>@ngrx/router-store</code>.</li>\n<li>Run <code>npm install</code> to install those dependencies. </li>\n<li>By default, will update  <code>src/app/app.module.ts</code> > <code>imports</code> array with <code><a href=\"api/router-store/StoreRouterConnectingModule#forRoot\" class=\"code-anchor\">StoreRouterConnectingModule.forRoot()</a></code>. If you provided flags then the command will attempt to locate and update module found by the flags.</li>\n<li>If the flag <code>--standalone</code> is provided, it adds <code><a href=\"api/router-store/provideRouterStore\" class=\"code-anchor\">provideRouterStore</a>()</code> into the application config.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"installing-with-npm\">Installing with <code>npm</code><a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/router-store/install#installing-with-npm\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<p>For more information on using <code>npm</code> check out the docs <a href=\"https://docs.npmjs.com/cli/install\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\n<code-example language=\"sh\">\nnpm install @ngrx/router-store --save\n</code-example>\n<h2 id=\"installing-with-yarn\">Installing with <code>yarn</code><a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/router-store/install#installing-with-yarn\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<p>For more information on using <code>yarn</code> check out the docs <a href=\"https://yarnpkg.com/getting-started/usage#installing-all-the-dependencies\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\n<code-example language=\"sh\">\nyarn add @ngrx/router-store\n</code-example>\n\n</div>\n\n<!-- links to this doc:\n - guide/router-store\n-->\n<!-- links from this doc:\n - api/router-store/StoreRouterConnectingModule\n - api/router-store/StoreRouterConnectingModule#forRoot\n - api/router-store/provideRouterStore\n - guide/router-store/install#installation\n - guide/router-store/install#installing-with-ng-add\n - guide/router-store/install#installing-with-npm\n - guide/router-store/install#installing-with-yarn\n - guide/router-store/install#optional-ng-add-flags\n - https://angular.io/cli/add\n - https://docs.npmjs.com/cli/install\n - https://github.com/ngrx/platform/edit/master/projects/ngrx.io/content/guide/router-store/install.md?message=docs%3A%20describe%20your%20change...\n - https://yarnpkg.com/getting-started/usage#installing-all-the-dependencies\n-->"
